enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve creating a predicate based on an input object, with the second method also accepting an Equator for comparison.
Both methods handle the case where the input object is null by returning a NullPredicate.
The test method in EqualPredicate evaluates whether the input object equals the stored value, which can be used to construct assertions for the equalPredicate method.
The test method in NullPredicate evaluates whether the input object is null, which can be used to construct assertions for the null handling in the equalPredicate method.
